\maketitle
\textbf{by John Tait}

A supplement to the classic rabbit epic \emph{Watership Down} by the late Richard Adams: a full index to the print version and a glossary.

\emph{Watership Down} is the best book in the whole world. It was the basis for a smash hit 1978 film of the same name. I'm still recovering from that experience, as we all are.

\emph{Watership Down} © 1972 Richard Adams.

Comments welcome: \href{mailto:johngtait@gmail.com}{johngtait@gmail.com}. Please write and say hello if you like this.

\rule{\linewidth}{0.5pt}
\begin{center}
This is a work in progress. It isn't finished. Up to p.123.
\end{center}



\rule{\linewidth}{0.5pt}

\section*{Glossary of Lapine (rabbit language) and other terms}
\label{sec-1}

From the book, or paraphrased from the book. Lapine terms are capitialized when used as a rabbit name, and are in italics.


\begin{description}
\item[{Dea ex Machina}] goddess in the machine (Latin)
\item[{\emph{elil}}] enemies
\item[{\emph{embleer}}] stinking, smell of fox
\item[{\emph{flayrah}}] appetizing food
\item[{\emph{fu Inl\'{e}}}] after moonrise
\item[{\emph{Frith}}] God, also the sun
\item[{\emph{Frithrah!}}] exclamation. Likely to be 'Lord God!'
\item[{\emph{Hlao}}] any small concavity in the grass where moisture may collect (name of Pipkin in Lapine)
\item[{\emph{Hoi, Hoi u embleer Hrair, M' saigon ul\'{e} hraka vair}}] Hoi, Hoi, the stinking Thousand, We meet them even when we stop to pass our droppings
\item[{\emph{homba}}] fox (pl: hombil)
\item[{\emph{Hrair}}] a lot
\item[{\emph{Hrairoo}}] Little Thousand (name of Fiver in Lapine)
\item[{\emph{hraka}}] droppings
\item[{\emph{hrududu}}] motor vehicle (pl: \emph{hrududil})
\item[{\emph{Labernum}}] Poison-tree (name of rabbit in Cowslip's Warren)
\item[{\emph{lendri}}] dog
\item[{\emph{ni-Frith}}] noon
\item[{\emph{Nildro-Hain}}] Song of the Blackbird (name of doe in Cowslip's Warren)
\item[{outskirter}] rank-and-file ordinary rabbit
\item[{\emph{Owsla}}] strong or clever rabbits surrounding the Chief Rabbit
\item[{\emph{-roo}}] little (name suffix)
\item[{\emph{Sayn lay narn, marli?}}] Is grounsel nice, mother? (muttered by Pipkin in sleep)
\item[{\emph{silflay}}] go above ground to feed
\item[{\emph{tharn}}] paralysis caused by fear and exhaustion
\item[{\emph{Thlayli}}] Furhead (name of Bigwig in Lapine)
\item[{\emph{Threarah}}] Lord Rowan Tree (name of Chief Rabbit of Sandleford in Lapine)
\item[{\emph{U Hrair}}] The Thousand ('All the enemies' in Lapine)
\item[{\emph{yona}}] hedgehog (pl: \emph{yonil})
\end{description}

\rule{\linewidth}{0.5pt}

